-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1D Stencil Kernel in different implementations
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Gabriele.Jost@intel.com
Element-wise stencil update. Tests fine grained nearest neighbor communication.

- sequential
- MPI
- CnC-OCR
- Intel CnC


Shell scripts to build and run are provided in each sub-directory.
run_test.sh requires 2 input parameters: Number of grid points (NX) and number of iterations (NITER)

run_test.sh <NX> <NITER>

Example: ./run_test.sh 18 10

This will update 16 inner grid points, boundary values are set to 1.

Known issues:

- Current settings of boundary values yields to huge result values if run over many (>= 100) iterations.
- For mpi you have to manually modify the script to set the number of MPI ranks.
- cnc-ocr version requires habanero-rice-cnc-ocr-f833954 or later
